  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Aurora, IL?",
  "response": "Aurora, Illinois, known for its rich history and vibrant cultural scene, has several lesser-known sights that are worth a visit:\n\n1. **Leland Tower**: Once the tallest building in Illinois outside of Chicago, this historic skyscraper offers stunning architecture and a glimpse into Aurora\u2019s past.\n\n2. **Aurora Historical Society**: This small museum provides a comprehensive look at the city's history, featuring exhibits on local milestones and prominent figures.\n\n3. **SciTech Hands-On Museum**: While not entirely off the beaten path, this interactive museum offers over 200 exhibits that make science education fun for children and adults alike.\n\n4. **Phillips Park Zoo**: This charming zoo hosts a variety of animals and is smaller and more intimate than larger, more touristy zoos.\n\n5. **Aurora Regional Fire Museum**: A hidden gem, this museum showcases vintage fire trucks, gear, and exhibits that honor the history of firefighting in the region.\n\n6. **Island Park**: A scenic spot perfect for a peaceful day out, Island Park features walking paths, picnic areas, and beautiful views of the Fox River.\n\n7. **Aurora Aviation Museum**: Located at Aurora Municipal Airport, this museum offers insights into aviation history and displays vintage aircraft.\n\nExploring these lesser-known sights can provide a unique and enriching experience during your visit to Aurora, IL.",
